---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';

const title = "Drone-enhanced MR Remote Collaboration - Research Project";
const metaDescription = "Research on creating interfaces that intelligently adapt to individual user needs and preferences.";

// 项目信息
const project = {
    title: "Drone-enhanced MR Remote Collaboration",
    featuredImage: "/MyPage/images/drone-remote-collaboration-page/featured-image.png",
    description: "A novel Mixed Reality (MR) remote collaboration system that integrates a telepresence drone to overcome viewpoint limitations in traditional approaches, enabling more effective remote collaboration through independent spatial navigation.",
    dateStart: "2024-01",
    dateEnd: "Present",
    funding: "",
    collaborators: [
        {
            name: "Shihui Xu",
            role: "Co-Principal Investigator",
            affiliation: "Waseda University",
            avatar: "/MyPage/avatars/Avatar.svg"
        },
        {
            name: "Like Wu",
            role: "Research Collaborator",
            affiliation: "Waseda University",
            avatar: "/MyPage/avatars/Avatar.svg"
        },
        {
            name: "Wenjie Liao",
            role: "Research Collaborator",
            affiliation: "Waseda University",
            avatar: "/MyPage/avatars/Avatar.svg"
        },
        {
            name: "Shigeru Fujimura",
            role: "Supervisor",
            affiliation: "Waseda University",
            avatar: "/MyPage/avatars/Avatar.svg"
        }
    ],
    relatedPublications: [
        {
            title: "Exploring Human Reactions to Telepresence Drones: A User Study on Safety and Trust Using a Simulated Drone in a VR Environment",
            venue: "2025 IEEE Conference on Virtual Reality and 3D User Interfaces Abstracts and Workshops (VRW)",
            link: "/publications#vrw2025"
        },
        {
            title: "Enhancing Remote Collaboration Through Drone-Driven Agent and Mixed Reality",
            venue: "26th International Conference on Human-Computer Interaction (HCII 2024)",
            link: "/publications#hci2024"
        }
    ]
};
---

<MainLayout title={title} metaDescription={metaDescription}>
    <div class="container project-container">
        <div class="project-header">
            <h1 class="project-title">{project.title}</h1>
            <div class="project-meta">
                <span class="project-date">{project.dateStart} – {project.dateEnd}</span>
                <span class="project-funding">{project.funding}</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="project-featured-image">
            <img src={project.featuredImage} alt={project.title}>
        </div>
        
        <div class="project-content">
            <div class="project-main">
                <h2>Overview</h2>
                <p>This research presents a novel Mixed Reality (MR) remote collaboration system that integrates a telepresence drone to overcome viewpoint limitations in traditional approaches. Current MR systems typically restrict remote users to the local user's perspective or a fixed viewpoint, reducing spatial awareness and collaboration effectiveness.</p>
                
                <p>Our proposed system enables a remote user wearing a VR headset to independently navigate the local environment through a drone while guiding a local AR headset user. The drone embodies the remote user physically and virtually with an AR avatar. The system provides the remote user with a 3D reconstruction of the local environment, the local user's avatar, and real-time drone camera video to facilitate drone operation and collaboration.</p>
                
                <h2>Key Features</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Independent Spatial Navigation:</strong> Remote users can freely explore the local environment through drone control</li>
                    <li><strong>Embodied Communication:</strong> The drone serves as a physical proxy for the remote user with an AR avatar</li>
                    <li><strong>Enhanced Spatial Awareness:</strong> 3D environment reconstruction and real-time video streaming</li>
                    <li><strong>Intuitive Collaboration:</strong> Natural interaction between local and remote users through mixed reality interfaces</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h2>Research Impact</h2>
                <p>Our user study comparing the drone-enhanced MR system with traditional MR and 360-degree camera systems during inspection tasks revealed significant improvements:</p>
                
                <ul>
                    <li>Enhanced collaboration efficiency through independent spatial navigation</li>
                    <li>Improved social presence for both local and remote users</li>
                    <li>Better spatial presence for remote users compared to traditional systems</li>
                    <li>More effective task completion in inspection scenarios</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h2>Technical Implementation</h2>
                <p>The system consists of three core components:</p>
                
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>AR HMD (Local User):</strong> Provides spatial awareness and renders the remote user's avatar</li>
                    <li><strong>Telepresence Drone:</strong> Equipped with cameras for navigation and video streaming</li>
                    <li><strong>VR HMD (Remote User):</strong> Enables environment exploration and drone control</li>
                </ol>
                
                <h2>Methodology</h2>
                <p>Our research employs a mixed-methods approach combining quantitative experimentation with qualitative insights:</p>
                
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>System Development:</strong> Implementation of the drone-enhanced MR remote collaboration system with AR and VR interfaces</li>
                    <li><strong>Comparative Study:</strong> Evaluation of our system against traditional MR and 360-degree camera approaches</li>
                    <li><strong>Task Performance Analysis:</strong> Assessment of collaboration efficiency in inspection tasks</li>
                    <li><strong>User Experience Evaluation:</strong> Measurement of social presence, spatial presence, and system usability</li>
                </ol>
                
                <h2>Current Progress</h2>
                <p>We have completed the following milestones in our research:</p>
                
                <ul>
                    <li>Successfully developed and implemented the drone-enhanced MR remote collaboration system</li>
                    <li>Conducted comprehensive user studies comparing our system with traditional approaches</li>
                    <li>Analyzed and documented the experimental results demonstrating improved collaboration efficiency</li>
                    <li>Completed a research paper and submitted it to an international journal for publication</li>
                    <li>Identified key design guidelines for future drone-enhanced MR remote collaboration systems</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h2>Future Directions</h2>
                <p>Based on our findings, we plan to explore several promising directions:</p>
                
                <ul>
                    <li>Integration of advanced computer vision techniques for more accurate environment reconstruction</li>
                    <li>Development of semi-autonomous drone behaviors to reduce remote user workload</li>
                    <li>Exploration of multi-drone scenarios for complex collaborative tasks</li>
                    <li>Investigation of long-term usage patterns and adaptation strategies</li>
                    <li>Application of the system in various domains such as industrial inspection, maintenance, and training</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="video-container">
                    <iframe 
                        src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/yohV-IvWXZA"
                        title="Drone Remote Collaboration Demo"
                        frameborder="0"
                        allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
                        allowfullscreen>
                    </iframe>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="project-sidebar">
                <div class="sidebar-section">
                    <h3 class="sidebar-title">Team Members</h3>
                    <div class="team-members">
                        {project.collaborators.map(member => (
                            <div class="team-member">
                                <img src={member.avatar} alt={member.name} class="member-avatar">
                                <div class="member-info">
                                    <div class="member-name">{member.name}</div>
                                    <div class="member-role">{member.role}, {member.affiliation}</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        ))}
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="sidebar-section">
                    <h3 class="sidebar-title">Related Publications</h3>
                    <ul class="related-publications">
                        {project.relatedPublications.map(pub => (
                            <li>
                                <a href={pub.link}>{pub.title}</a>
                                <span class="publication-venue">{pub.venue}</span>
                            </li>
                        ))}
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</MainLayout>

<style>
    .project-container {
        padding: 2rem 0 4rem;
    }
    
    .project-header {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    
    .project-title {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        font-weight: 400;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        font-family: var(--font-serif);
        color: var(--color-text);
        position: relative;
        display: inline-block;
        padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    
    .project-title:after {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        bottom: 0;
        left: 25%;
        width: 50%;
        height: 2px;
        background-color: var(--color-primary);
    }
    
    .project-meta {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        gap: 2rem;
        color: var(--color-text-light);
    }
    
    .project-featured-image {
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
        border-radius: 5px;
        overflow: hidden;
        box-shadow: var(--shadow);
        max-width: 800px;
        margin-left: auto;
        margin-right: auto;
    }
    
    .project-featured-image img {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        display: block;
        object-fit: cover;
    }
    
    .project-content {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
        gap: 3rem;
    }
    
    .project-main h2 {
        font-family: var(--font-serif);
        font-weight: 500;
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
        color: var(--color-text);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    
    .project-main h2:first-child {
        margin-top: 0;
    }
    
    .project-main p, 
    .project-main ul, 
    .project-main ol {
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        color: var(--color-text);
    }
    
    .project-main ul, 
    .project-main ol {
        padding-left: 1.5rem;
    }
    
    .project-main li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    
    .project-main strong {
        color: var(--color-primary);
        font-weight: 500;
    }
    
    .project-sidebar {
        position: sticky;
        top: 6rem;
        align-self: start;
    }
    
    .sidebar-section {
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
        background-color: var(--color-background);
        border-radius: 5px;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }
    
    .sidebar-title {
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        font-weight: 500;
        margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
        padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
        position: relative;
        color: var(--color-text);
    }
    
    .sidebar-title::after {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        bottom: 0;
        left: 0;
        width: 30px;
        height: 2px;
        background-color: var(--color-primary);
    }
    
    .team-members {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 1rem;
    }
    
    .team-member {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 1rem;
    }
    
    .member-avatar {
        width: 50px;
        height: 50px;
        border-radius: 50%;
        object-fit: cover;
        border: 2px solid var(--color-primary-light);
    }
    
    .member-info {
        flex-grow: 1;
    }
    
    .member-name {
        font-weight: 500;
        color: var(--color-text);
    }
    
    .member-role {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: var(--color-text-light);
    }
    
    .related-publications li {
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    
    .related-publications a {
        display: block;
        color: var(--color-primary);
        margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
        font-weight: 500;
    }
    
    .related-publications a:hover {
        color: var(--color-accent);
    }
    
    .publication-venue {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: var(--color-text-light);
        font-style: italic;
    }
    
    .video-container {
        margin-top: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        position: relative;
        padding-top: 56.25%; /* 16:9 aspect ratio */
    }
    
    .video-container iframe {
        position: absolute;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        border: 0;
    }
    
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .project-content {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
        
        .project-sidebar {
            position: static;
            margin-top: 2rem;
        }
    }
</style> 